{"tid":2060874,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"亞裔激進左翼組織籲拜登對中國放軟手腳，拜登不作保證","createTime":"2020-06-12T03:36:27.000Z","updateTime":"2020-06-12T10:13:32.000Z","uid":207710,"like":16,"dislike":106,"uniUserReply":57,"replies":[{"pid":"50fc31c7d333497509226f8c0bca8daf50659da0","tid":2060874,"uid":207710,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-12T03:36:27.000Z","msg":"Biden Camp Tries to Walk Fine Line on China<br />\n<br />\nIn May, representatives of progressive Asian American organizations held a virtual meeting with Joe Biden&rsquo;s camp to raise concern about the Democratic candidate&rsquo;s China policy, in particular his efforts to demonstrate he was tougher on Beijing than President Donald Trump, which risked exposing Chinese Americans to backlash.<br />\n<br />\nThe meeting, which was described by three people familiar with it, followed the airing in April of a political ad by the Biden campaign titled &ldquo;Unprepared,&rdquo; denouncing Trump as weak on China. The ad&mdash;which faulted Trump for having &ldquo;rolled over for the Chinese&rdquo; and letting 40,000 travelers from China into the country after he imposed a flight ban in response to the coronavirus&mdash;provoked anger and dismay among progressive Democrats and Asian American advocates, who felt it risked fomenting anti-Chinese sentiment.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;We made our concerns clear and communicated very strongly that we wanted to see the campaign stop using this xenophobic and anti-China rhetoric,&rdquo; said one person present at the meeting with Amit Jani, who serves as the Asian American Pacific Islander outreach director on Biden&rsquo;s campaign. &ldquo;It was clear we were not the first group to raise this concern.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nThe Biden campaign offered no guarantees. But it did respond to the appeal&mdash;which followed the publication of a letter by Asian American groups criticizing Biden&rsquo;s ad&mdash;by slightly softening its approach in subsequent ads. Instead of highlighting Trump&rsquo;s apparent acquiescence to China, the new ads criticized his weakness in challenging the Chinese Communist Party and President Xi Jinping. They also stopped promoting the claim that Trump allowed tens of thousands of potentially infected travelers from China into the country.<br />\n<br />\nBut some Asian American advocates say Biden hasn&rsquo;t gone far enough.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The Biden campaign has responded to concerns we and others have raised and dialed down the tone of the most inflammatory rhetoric in the original ad,&rdquo; said Tobita Chow, the director of Justice Is Global, a Chicago-based advocacy group. &ldquo;Even so, the whole messaging strategy of trying to compete to prove who is tougher is going to continue to feed into this rise of anti-Asian racism. And it&rsquo;s going to continue to poison the U.S.-China relationship.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;It is clear that Biden&rsquo;s choice is to double down on this [anti-China] messaging,&rdquo; added Grace Pai, the director of movement politics for Asian American Midwest Progressives, who helped organize the letter-writing effort. &ldquo;The strategy of going to war with the Trump camp over China is still consistent.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nAn informal advisor to the Biden campaign told Foreign Policy that the former vice president is clear-eyed about the need to coexist with China and to work together to resolve pressing global challenges, from the effort to curb greenhouse gas emissions that fuel global warming to containing the coronavirus and convincing North Korea to dismantle its nuclear weapons program. But the advisor said Biden will continue to call out China on a number of issues, including its mass incarceration of Muslim Uighurs, its suppression of information about the coronavirus, and its promotion of unfair trade practices.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;I don&rsquo;t think anyone wants a knife fight,&rdquo; the advisor said. &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t get the sense that the vice president wants a race to the bottom on who can be tougher on China. But Trump has been very much standing with Xi, and so this is something that of course the vice president would be focused on.&rdquo;...<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/06/11/biden-presidential-election-china-trump-asian-americans/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2020%2F06%2F11%2Fbiden-presidential-election-china-trump-asian-americans%2F&d=isL%2BTa9V4QtjyiE8eWWd0jDyw%2Fr9SRfH8QBX8OZV2FM%3D&h=c971d45d\" target=\"_blank\">https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/06/11/biden-presidential-election-china-trump-asian-americans/</a>"},{"pid":"a94a8d5ace8cb16a790c9f7bb745347365939642","tid":2060874,"uid":155095,"like":75,"dislike":0,"score":75,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-12T03:39:24.000Z","msg":"China Joe 使鬼保證咩 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"93f442d272dfd00781dd5c775c9ea9acf03b17e5","tid":2060874,"uid":336575,"like":57,"dislike":1,"score":56,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-12T03:41:26.000Z","msg":"嘩，咁都仲唔係恐怖組織<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/donno.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/donno.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n直程賣國"},{"pid":"105472846478761d3c5747bcb69bc2ca691ddde9","tid":2060874,"uid":25468,"like":28,"dislike":1,"score":27,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-12T03:41:46.000Z","msg":"拜登：要保證先信即係唔當我係兄弟啫"},{"pid":"e451d4b7e09a59d038c4dfec0b2b78396ee8955f","tid":2060874,"uid":19527,"like":45,"dislike":0,"score":45,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-12T03:45:02.000Z","msg":"拜登做到總統香港人可以準備入集中營<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"175fa02d62587729c24ac4ddf1ff4a54497eae29","tid":2060874,"uid":124711,"like":44,"dislike":1,"score":43,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-12T03:47:59.000Z","msg":"拜登：咪咁撚揚啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/hoho.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid"